## Project Detail

- TARGET PAGE: Project Detail
- Description: A single-project view that consolidates backlog, roadmap items, tickets, PRs, agent-run history, and action widgets. It integrates with the Project Management Automation layer (roadmaps, ticketing automation, PR summarization, release notes generation, CI/CD integrations via agents) and connects to supporting pages: Ticket Board (Kanban board with agent automation rules, bulk edits, sprint planning), CI & Integrations Page (repository links, CI/CD connectors, deployment targets, integration health with logs/test triggers), and Projects Dashboard (developer-centric hub with roadmaps, active tickets, PRs, releases, CI status, and agent-suggested actions).

- Core Goals:
  - Provide a coherent, responsive, and highly interactive single-project cockpit.
  - Reflect Roadmaps, Backlog, Tickets, PRs, and Agent History in a unified layout.
  - Enable agent-driven actions (triage, release notes, summarization) with explicit auditing and reversibility.
  - Offer action widgets and an Approvals/Cronjobs integration surface for scheduled workflows and governance.

- Connected Features:
  - Project Management Automation: Roadmaps, ticket automation, PR summarization, release notes generation, CI/CD integrations via agents.
  - Agent Run History: Audit trails, run artifacts, and traceable inter-agent messages.

---

## Overview

- The Project Detail page serves as the Command Center for a single LifeOps project. It aggregates:
  - Project header (name, owners, status, integrations)
  - Backlog section with quick-add and status indicators
  - Roadmap items (timeline, status, owners)
  - Tickets and PRs (summary, status, assignees)
  - Agent-run history (recent runs, outcomes, links to run artifacts)
  - Action widgets (start agent runs, generate release notes, run CI checks)
- The UI follows a dark, dense, developer-centric design system with a focus on clarity, auditability, and fast scanning.

