## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] The Project Detail page renders with header, backlog, roadmaps, tickets, PRs, agent history, and action widgets, each backed by safe data-loading flows (no crashes if data is missing).
- [ ] All array operations guard against null/undefined: e.g., (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- [ ] State initialization: all arrays use useState<T[]>([]) defaults; object states initialized safely.
- [ ] Actions (Run Agent, Generate Release Notes, Schedule Cronjobs) create AgentRun/CronJob records and reflect immediately in AgentHistoryPanel.
- [ ] Bulk edit and quick-add work without throwing on empty data; UI shows appropriate empty states.
- [ ] Data fetches are resilient: if a dataset is missing, the UI renders without crashing and shows empty-state indicators.
- [ ] Security: protected routes require authentication; unauthorized users cannot mutate project data; audit logs are created for agent runs and cronjob actions.
- [ ] UI consistency: components adhere to the provided visual style, typography, spacing, and color tokens.

